body:
Not a meaty issue, but didn't come across this before. Please let me know if you need more info.

Wanted to reverse the sign in a (gmt) generated tif-file. The file is correctly made, but `gmt` complains about `proj`-string.
There is no `proj` data in the input file.

```
$ gmt grdinfo alt_bat_50m.tif
alt_bat_50m.tif: Title: Grid imported via GDAL
alt_bat_50m.tif: Command: 
alt_bat_50m.tif: Remark: 
alt_bat_50m.tif: Gridline node registration used [Cartesian grid]
alt_bat_50m.tif: Grid file format: gd = Import/export through GDAL
alt_bat_50m.tif: x_min: 21897 x_max: 727780 x_inc: 49.9987958634 name: x n_columns: 14119
alt_bat_50m.tif: y_min: 7060993 y_max: 8271670 y_inc: 49.9990501363 name: y n_rows: 24215
alt_bat_50m.tif: v_min: 1 v_max: 3914.31005859 name: z
alt_bat_50m.tif: scale_factor: 1 add_offset: 0

$ gmt grdmath alt_bat_50m.tif -1 MUL = alt_bat_50m-inv.tif=gd:GTiff
ERROR 1: PROJ: proj_create: unrecognized format / unknown name
grdmath [ERROR]: gmt_gdalwrite failed to convert the proj4 string

 to WKT
```

Need something to test. Can it be that "-inv" in the file name?
This worked fine for me
```
grdmath C:\v\level1_merge_qgis_latlon_cut.tif -1 MUL = lixo.tif=gd:GTiff
```

Do not happen when creating .nc, but `gd:GTiff`:

```
$ gmt grdmath alt_bat_50m.tif -1 MUL = test.nc

$ gmt grdmath alt_bat_50m.tif -1 MUL = test.tif=gd:GTiff
ERROR 1: PROJ: proj_create: unrecognized format / unknown name
grdmath [ERROR]: gmt_gdalwrite failed to convert the proj4 string

 to WKT
```

Tried to cut, got:

```
gmt grdcut alt_bat_50m.tif -R707780/727780/7060993/7080993 -Gtemp.nc

...20...30...40...50...60...70...80...90...100 - done.
```

The last (in this case - empty) line usually outputs the proj-string, right?

```
$ gmt grdinfo alt_bat_50m.tif 
alt_bat_50m.tif: Title: Grid imported via GDAL
alt_bat_50m.tif: Command: 
alt_bat_50m.tif: Remark: 
alt_bat_50m.tif: Gridline node registration used [Cartesian grid]

alt_bat_50m.tif: x_min: 21897 x_max: 727780 x_inc: 49.9987958634 name: x n_columns: 14119
alt_bat_50m.tif: y_min: 7060993 y_max: 8271670 y_inc: 49.9990501363 name: y n_rows: 24215
alt_bat_50m.tif: v_min: 1 v_max: 3914.31005859 name: z
alt_bat_50m.tif: scale_factor: 1 add_offset: 0
[......................]
```

So according to `gdalinfo` there is coordinate info, but `gmt` does not show it?

Apparently it's not being able to convert the WKT of that file into proj4. Note that the ``ERROR xx:`` messages are issued by GDAL, not GMT.
Is this error fatal or the file created nevertheless?
Not fatal at all. The command succeeds.
And is it a grid coming from the Arc World? I see time-to-time mentions that not all WKTs are convertible to PROJ4. Maybe that's one of them.

I'm ~~almost certain~~ think that this grid was made (by me) based on a whole bunch of input files with `gmt nearneighbor` (https://docs.generic-mapping-tools.org/latest/nearneighbor.html), so should _not_ be from Arc world (can't stand it).
If it's a strange case, just close the issue. I can report again if I come across it (with more substance).
I'm just wondering where that WKT that is resisting to translation is coming from. Honestly, I don't know what's the problem. Just interpreting the error messages.
Does it not say the coordinate system is UNKNOWN in gdalinfo? What exactly is the WKT string here?

I'm closing this one. I think the grid was originally created with gmt, but I probably did something to it (e.g. cut it) so the `proj`-stuff got messed up.

Will report again if I have a similar issue (_with_ supporting data).

title: Complaints about proj4 string
